                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="53640" author="pjones" created="Fri, 8 Mar 2013 20:14:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Landed for 2.4&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="53170" author="di.wang" created="Thu, 28 Feb 2013 05:01:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,5555&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,5555&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="53141" author="di.wang" created="Wed, 27 Feb 2013 20:42:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, I am working on the patch, the dot lustre and obf had a few other problem as well. I will post the fix soon. Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="53116" author="hdoreau" created="Wed, 27 Feb 2013 10:08:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The problem is that the aforementioned patch I7483b0f023e4e3de6597da58d3d9f3e96c0d53b7&lt;br/&gt;
modified mdo_unlink() to make it call the corresponding method of the parent instead&lt;br/&gt;
of the one of the child. Therefore, dot_lustre_mdd_unlink (that always return -EPERM)&lt;br/&gt;
was never invoked.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the following patch, that fixes the issue, I&apos;ve added a check to mdt_reint_unlink()&lt;br/&gt;
to make sure that we not trying to unlink .lustre/&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,5544&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,5544&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="52970" author="pjones" created="Mon, 25 Feb 2013 11:31:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Di&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Could you please look into this one?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
